rComments: RUN WHEN YOU SEE HER NAME!! She is the worst. Her explanations are very ambiguous, her PowerPoint don't are useless and don't match her explanations.  Her midterm is a trap because her final is on a whole new level. AVOID HER!
professor whose expectation for her students do not match the quality of her teaching. Has no mastery of her subject beyond her notes. You can't learn with her
Very kind  teacher but extremely disorganized. Isn't confortable with the class material and doesn't look like she prepares her class.

Elle passe la moitié du cours à chercher la formulation de ses phrases. Ses explications ne sont pas très détaillées et ne préparent pas très bien aux examens. Il faut faire attention à la lecture!! Ce n'est pas parce qu'elle n'aborde pas un sujet dans un jugement ou un avis consultatif qu'il n'est pas important. Il faut mémoriser chaque lecture
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Très bonne mais il faut être attentif! Attendez-vous à lire beaucoup mais Mona Paré est une excellente prof. Ses examens sont très bien si vous êtes préparé!
RUN WHILE YOU CAN! RUN WHILE YOU CAN! RUN WHILE YOU CAN! RUN WHILE YOU CAN! RUN WHILE YOU CAN! RUN WHILE YOU CAN! RUN WHILE YOU CAN!

Dry lecturer. Her optional classes mainly consist of presentations, essays and take home exams (sometimes, all three). Take home exams are tricky but doable. Course load may be heavy because of this. However, you can definitely put in the work for a good grade, and she gives good feedback.

Made the material a complete snoozefest. She is a nice individual and clearly cares about her students, but 3 hours in her class will feel like 9. Zero practice exams or exercices. Midterm was a walk in the park and then final was a complete 180. Loses focus often. Avoid if you can.
Very boring professor. 3 hour classes seem like 6 hours. Subject is interesting but her teaching is beyond monotone.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Assigns heavy readings, and her class lectures are long and dry. In a 3 hour lecture she gives one 10-minute break, and sometimes she starts sooner, which doesn't make the lecture anymore tolerable. Seems like she depends heavily on the textbook readings for her lectures; doesn't demonstrate much knowledge beyond it.

Her exams are fair. Students at OU are so used to be coddled and have professors give them open books exams, that they find it a crime to use their brains a little bit more. If you're VERY MUCH interested in PIL, you'll find that her assessment methods are the sure way to absorb what you learned.

Most BORING class ever! She tells us that the book isn't mandatory, but still expects us to read it; make up ur mind!!! Furthermore, who the HELL gives a final exam worth 80% of your final grade and have it be CLOSED BOOK!!! Let's pray to God that you at the very least grade it easily and generously!
Overall, she is a good prof and I would recommend her. Lectures aren't too dry, and she brings interesting point of views. Very knowledgeable.

I liked her, had her twice in Public International law and International Human Rights law. She's organized, a nice person, a little withdrawn so might seem boring. If you have no interest in international relations, well, you might feel lost in class.
